Subject to the other provisions of this Act the functions of the Council shall be to:
(a) keep itself fully appraised of the policy of the Government in matters concerning arts and to disseminate that policy;
keep itself fully appraised of the policy of the Government in matters concerning arts and to disseminate that policy;
(b) serve as the supreme advisory body at national level on policy and decisions on all forms of arts in the country;
serve as the supreme advisory body at national level on policy and decisions on all forms of arts in the country;
(c) provide quality artistic leadership in performing and visual arts;
provide quality artistic leadership in performing and visual arts;
(d) develop, promote, regulate and encourage all forms of amateur and professional arts on a national basis in conjunction with the associations and the Government;
develop, promote, regulate and encourage all forms of amateur and professional arts on a national basis in conjunction with the associations and the Government;
(e) assist the formation of associations or organisations and encourage them to register as national arts associations so as to represent different groups of associations in Zambia and to encourage the affiliation of those associations to the appropriate international organisations;
assist the formation of associations or organisations and encourage them to register as national arts associations so as to represent different groups of associations in Zambia and to encourage the affiliation of those associations to the appropriate international organisations;
(f) assist, financially or otherwise, any group or individual in representing Zambia in any artistic activity within or outside Zambia;
assist, financially or otherwise, any group or individual in representing Zambia in any artistic activity within or outside Zambia;
(g) assist, financially or otherwise, in conjunction with the Government, any citizen of Zambia in obtaining relevant training within or outside Zambia;
