(1) The Registrar shall refuse to register any association or organisation as a national arts association if he is satisfied— (a) that the association or organisation does not exist; (b) that the registration of the association or organisation would be against the public interest; (c) that the name under which the association or organisation wishes to be registered is identical, or similar, to the name of any existing national arts association or any society or body registered, or exempted from registration, under the Societies Act; or [ Cap. 119 ] (d) the constitution or rules of the association or organisation are in his opinion repugnant to, or inconsistent with, the provisions of any law for the time being in force in Zambia.
